<HEADLINE>
FT  10 MAY 91 / Letter: Holding on to Gibraltar
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   From Mr DAVID GLAZIER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Sir, It has been fascinating to read the various reports on Premier Felipe
Gonza1ez's official visit to London. I believe that on most matters his
views and opinions are correct and clearly there is much common ground which
should enable Spain and the UK to play important roles in the enhancement of
the European Community.
However, the British government should continue its present position with
regard to Gibraltar. Britain should not, under any circumstances, consider
changing the terms of the Treaty of Utrecht until such time as Spain
indicates its willingness to relinquish its sovereignty of Ceuta and Melilla
to Morocco. By the same token, I can see no harm in permitting the Spaniards
to use the airport in Gibraltar - after all, it is closer to the town hall
in La Linea than it is to Government House]
David Glazier,
6 Bow Field,
Hook, Basingstoke,
Hampshire
</TEXT>
