<HEADLINE>
FT  10 MAY 91 / Technology (Worth Watching): Software's test of strength
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DELLA BRADSHAW
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
ERRORS in software could be costing British companies millions of pounds a
year because data processing departments fail to test applications
rigorously, according to a new survey.
The report carried out for the UK arm of the software testing specialist
Compuware, of Michigan, surveyed more than 600 IBM mainframe sites in the
UK. It revealed that while simple and routine testing was being carried out
on most sites, complex software testing was being overlooked.
While 86 per cent of sites routinely undertook testing of a new program in
isolation and 93 per cent undertook testing to ensure the new program worked
with existing software, only 32 per cent of sites tested the software when a
program was adapted.
Compuware: US, 313 737 7300; UK, 0582 477555.
