FT  10 MAY 91 / Technology (Worth Watching): Dull IT tasks shown the door
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DELLA BRADSHAW
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
PAYING an outside company to run your computer operations may make it easier
to balance the accounts. But many companies worry that this may reduce their
ability to react quickly when they need a system which will give the company
a competitive edge.
To provide the benefits of facilities management without the drawbacks,
Gatton Synthesis, of Redhill, Surrey, has introduced a service which takes
over the routine tasks of data processing while leaving the IT department to
concentrate on the strategic development work.
Such mundane jobs include everything from software maintenance,
documentation and the running of help desks to applications such as accounts
or payroll.
Gatton Synthesis believes that Sam (systems application maintenance), as the
service is called, can help the customer overcome continuing shortages in
skilled software staff, as well as carrying out a less expensive and more
cost-accountable support service to the business.
Gatton Synthesis: UK, 0737 774100.
