PRESIDENT George Bush yesterday urged American Hispanic groups to 'sally
forth' to Capitol Hill to lobby for his proposed North American Free Trade
Agreement (Nafta) or risk a failure which would send an 'unconscionable'
signal to South America.
Mr Bush, who has played a big role in the administration's campaign for the
Nafta, praised President Carlos Salinas of Mexico for 'taking that country
that we all love and moving it in a direction that we can all admire.'
