Congress cannot amend.
The president has asked for that authority for the Uruguay Round, the Nafta,
and his Enterprise for the Americas trade and debt initiative for Latin
America.
Mr Bush is expected to win the fast-track fight in the Senate but to have a
harder time in the House of Representatives. A poll released yesterday of
three-quarters of the House members found half saying they would vote
against it.
