Sheikh Hasina, who has just returned to Dhaka after visiting the affected
areas, made a scathing attack on Mrs Zia's government for its handling of
the crisis. Much of the relief work is, in fact, being carried out by the
army, which is providing food and medical aid to the victims and tents as
temporary shelters.
