<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
NEWS that Jacuzzi, the whirlpool bathmaker owned by Britain's Hanson group,
might bid Dollars 20 a share for Eljer Industries sent the potential target
group's stock soaring by Dollars 8 3/4 to Dollars 21 7/8 yesterday.
An offer at this price would value the Texas-based manufacturer of plumbing,
heating, and ventilation products at about Dollars 145m (Pounds 86m).
Yesterday, Mr Roy Jacuzzi, president of the California-based company, said
