than enthusiastic. Describing Jacuzzi's approach as 'unsolicited', it said
that the matter would be discussed at the next scheduled board meeting on
June 18.
Eljer's net profits fell from Dollars 7.27m to Dollars 2.48m in 1990. Sales
were Dollars 449.2m.
Hanson is thought to have a stake of less than 5 per cent.
