<HEADLINE>
FT  09 MAY 91 / The Lex Column: Rolls-Royce
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The latest job cuts at Rolls-Royce come as little surprise after the Pounds
50m provided against last year's profits. The stated reasons for the
cutbacks, though, beg the question whether this sort of trimming should not
have been carried out before. The repercussions of the Gulf crisis, airline
finances and Defence Ministry cutbacks are all convenient enough
justifications. But the running down of the helicopter factory at Leavesden
is the sort of move British Aerospace might have made without waiting for
the political climate to be right. Rolls-Royce shares have recently been
stalled by the uncertainty over big orders for the Trent engine. New
evidence that the cost base is being tackled will reassure those convinced
of the stock's long-term attractions.
</TEXT>
