If you feel a compulsion to watch television there is Floyd On Oz (8.00
BBC2) in which the intrepid gastronaut takes a train to the Australian
interior and on the way feeds four fashion models, a young camel named
Camilla, and the train driver.
This Week (8.30 ITV) shows how arms manufacturers are endeavouring to cash
in on the 'smart' weapons which supposedly won the Gulf War. The programme
tells how the Patriot missile system failed to intercept the last Scud fired
in the war because one unit was undergoing maintenance and another failed to
register a threat, so that 28 Americans were killed.
