<HEADLINE>
FT  09 MAY 91 / Christian democrat guilty of tax evasion
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DAVID MARSH
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   BONN
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
A long-running court case into illegal financing of German political parties
came to an end yesterday when Mr Walther Leisler Kiep, treasurer of the
Christian Democratic Union, was fined DM675,000 (Pounds 228,000) on tax
evasion charges, reports David Marsh from Bonn.
Mr Kiep was found guilty in the Dusseldorf district court of depriving the
state of DM7.4m in tax revenues by operating a fraudulent money-gathering
scheme for channelling donations from big German companies.
The system, under which companies were able to transfer untaxed funds to the
CDU through a Cologne-based foundation, was in place between 1971 and 1981.
</TEXT>
